{"TopicId":190761,"ForumId":20,"TopicTitle":"Dying Battery Mod","CreatedByName":"Probus","CreatedById":102512,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-01-01T20:15:24Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"Probus","CreatedById":102512,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-01-01T20:15:24Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI don\u0027t remember anyone ever making a mod that simulated the decay of batteries over time (even space/temperature).\u00A0 What starts out at 100 EC is probably quite a bit less after a few years.\u00A0 Maybe it could be added to one of \u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/83952-nertea/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u002283952\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/83952-nertea/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@Nertea\u003C/a\u003E\u0027s mods or possibly a feature of something like DangIt!.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nA mod that reduced batteries\u00A0linearly would be a good place to start.\u00A0 You could then fancy it up to make it non-linear, based on battery materials, and/or real world data.\u00A0 Also, non-rechargeable batteries could be added to the mod.\u00A0 If you were really felling creative, battery failure modes like shorting and leaking\u00A0could be added.\u00A0 Catching fire probably wouldn\u0027t happen unless they were in an atmosphere of some sort.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"zer0Kerbal","CreatedById":190933,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-01-02T01:55:31Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nmaybe this:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022\u0022 data-controller=\u0022core.front.core.autosizeiframe\u0022 data-embedauthorid=\u0022159475\u0022 data-embedcontent=\u0022\u0022 data-embedid=\u0022embed231713997\u0022 scrolling=\u0022no\u0022 src=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/151164-173-real-battery-v17/\u0026amp;tab=comments\u0026amp;do=embed\u0026amp;commen